<div slot="quick-answer">
  <p><strong>Quick Answer:</strong> The best Chardonnay balances fruit, acidity, and oak integration while expressing its terroir. Top choices include Burgundy Grand Crus for complexity, California cult producers for power, and Australian icons for elegance. Expect to spend $40-200+ for exceptional quality.</p>
